          "name": "The Dragon",
          "description": "A grieving dragon hides on the premises; the locked room is its nest, the fortune its hoard.",
          "detail": "THE DRAGON — There is a small dragon living on the premises. It has been here for decades. It was grandma's. It is hiding, grieving, and deeply suspicious of the new owner. It will reveal itself when it's ready, not before. The locked room is its nest. The fortune is its hoard — grandma was its financial manager."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-empire",
          "name": "The Empire",
          "description": "Grandma was a crime lord; the player has legally inherited the operation and its dirty money.",
          "detail": "THE EMPIRE — Grandma was a crime lord. The house is the seat of an operation the player is now, legally, the head of. The locked room is the office. The fortune is dirty. People are going to come to the door expecting to do business, and they will not accept \"I didn't know\" as an answer."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-door",
          "name": "The Door",
          "description": "A portal to Regency England where grandma had a whole second life; the locked room is the threshold.",
          "detail": "THE DOOR — There is a portal in the house. It leads to Regency England — a specific year, a specific manor, a specific social circle. Grandma had a life there. A whole life, with a name and a reputation and relationships. The locked room is the threshold. The fortune came from there — two centuries of compound interest on a Regency-era investment."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-money",
          "name": "The Money",
          "description": "Nine hundred million in cash hidden in the house; the wrong people just learned it's here.",
          "detail": "THE MONEY — Nine hundred million dollars in cash. In the walls, under the floors, in the locked room stacked to the ceiling. It's not stolen — it's the result of something grandma did that the player doesn't understand yet. But someone else just found out it's here. The fortune on paper is a fraction of what's actually in the house, and the wrong people are doing the math."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-book",
          "name": "The Book",
          "description": "A working spellbook in a world that says magic is impossible; the locked room is where grandma practiced.",
          "detail": "THE BOOK — There is a fat, handwritten spellbook hidden in a bookcase. Everyone knows magic doesn't exist. Grandma apparently disagreed. The spells work — the player can test this — and the locked room is where grandma practiced. The fortune funded decades of private research into something the world says is impossible. The book is not the only copy. Grandma had colleagues."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-ship",
          "name": "The Ship",
          "description": "The house is a dormant spaceship; the locked room is the bridge, and it's waiting.",
          "detail": "THE SHIP — The house is a spaceship. Not metaphorically. The architecture is a shell around something much older and much more advanced. Grandma was its pilot, or its keeper, or its passenger — the distinction isn't clear yet. The locked room is the bridge. The house hasn't flown in decades, but it's not broken. It's waiting."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-house",
          "name": "The House",
          "description": "The house is pathologically bigger inside and still growing; the locked room is the one fixed point.",
          "detail": "THE HOUSE — The house is bigger on the inside. Not charmingly, not magically — pathologically. Hallways that shouldn't exist. Rooms that appear between visits. A staircase that goes down further than the foundation allows. The locked room is the only room that stays where it is. Grandma mapped the house obsessively — her notes are everywhere, contradictory, increasingly frantic. The house is growing. It has been growing since before grandma bought it. The fortune was what she spent trying to understand it."
        }
